# Cloudflare Workers static assets: exclude internal files from the deployed
# origin. The app fetches ONLY: index.html, attribution.html, app.js, config.js,
# styles.css, fonts/, and data/ EXCEPT the two build caches below.
# ATTRIBUTION.md must stay deployed — attribution.html fetches it at runtime.
#
# PWA (Phase 5.5): manifest.webmanifest, sw.js, and icons/ MUST deploy and are
# deliberately NOT excluded here. sw.js must be served from the root path so it
# can control the whole origin scope ("/"); nothing below blocks it.

# Build-pipeline caches (referenced only by scripts/*.mjs, never by app.js):
data/falling-fruit/us/cell-containment/
data/falling-fruit/us/access-cache/
data/inaturalist/us/access-cache/
# The GBIF sample/DWCA archives and the taxon-key artifact are build inputs, not
# served assets (taxon-keys.json is read by scripts at build time only).
data/inaturalist/taxon-keys.json

# Internal docs, agent queues, and research (not site content):
docs/
scripts/
prototype/
outputs/
KNOWN_ISSUES.md
AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md
README.md

# Repo/tooling files:
.git/
.gitignore
.claude/
.github/
.assetsignore
wrangler.jsonc
wrangler.beta.jsonc
# worker.js is the Worker entrypoint (wrangler `main`), not a served asset —
# keep it out of the origin so it can't be fetched at /worker.js.
worker.js
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
